DTU Highlights 2025

Delhi Technological University is ranked 66th by NIRF 2024 under the Overall category, 48th by NIRF 2024 under the University category, and 27th by NIRF 2024 under the Engineering category. Formerly known as Delhi College of Engineering, Delhi Technological University (DTU) was established in 1941.

DTU Delhi is accredited by the NAAC with an 'A' grade and NBA and is also approved by the University Grant Commission (UGC) and AICTE. The university is ISO-certified and earlier was affiliated with the University of Delhi. DTU University Delhi offers placement support to students and is visited by top companies such as Samsung, Microsoft, Zomato, and others. Delhi Technical University has a state-of-the-art infrastructure with multiple facilities available on the campus.

Delhi Technology University, through 17 departments, offers UG, PG, and various other courses to students. These courses are provided across the Engineering, Economics, and various other streams. Delhi Tech University is famous for its flagship courses which are MBA and BTech. The major highlights of Delhi Technological University (Delhi Technological University Campus) are tabulated below:

DTU History

Some of the historical facts of the DTU are given below:

  • 1941: Delhi College of Engineering, earlier known as Delhi Polytechnic was established
  • 1952: Affiliation with the University of Delhi and beginning of the formal degree-level programmes
  • 1962: Under the direct control of the Ministry of Education, Government of India
  • 1963: College administration shifted to Delhi Administration
  • 1996: Campus shifted to 164 acre of new campus established at Bawana Road, adjoining Sector-17, Rohini, Delhi-42
  • July 2009: Delhi College of Engineering became Delhi Technological University vide Delhi Act 6 of 2009

Commonly asked questions

Q: Do I need 75% to get into DTU?

A: 

For admission to most of the undergraduate and postgraduate courses offered at Delhi Technological University, students are required to score 50% to 60% minimum aggregate in their last qualifying degree or course to be eligible. A course-wise list of eligibility criteria for DTU admission is mentioned in the following table:

Course NameEligibility Criteria
BTech

Class 12 with 60%

BDes

A pass in Class 12

BBA

Class 12 with 50% 

MSc

 

Class 12 with 50% in Economics
MTech

Relevant UG degree with at least 60%

MDes

4-year UG with 55%

E-MBA

Any UG degree with 60%

E-MBAUG degree with 50%

MSc

Relevant BSc/ UG degree with 55% 

E-MBA

UG degree with 50%

PhD

Relevant PG degree with 55%

Hence, as per the table, it can be concluded that while all 75% scorers will be preferred at DTU, the minimum requirement to get admission and be eligible for DTU admission is comparatively low. 

Upvote

Q: Can I get direct admission into DTU for MBA?

A: 

Yes, it is possible. While DTU accepts CAT/ MAT or CMAT scores for admission to two of the MBA programmes offered by it. Admission to MBA programme in Family Business & Entrepreneurship and MBA in Entrepreneurship, Innovation & Venture Development is subject to candidates' performance at the undergraduate level and in the interview conducted by the university campus. For the remaining MBA courses, performance in CAT/ MAT or CMAT is considered along with students' performance in the last qualifying degree and interview conducted at the university-level. Additionally, all the candidates are required to meet the following eligibility criteria for admission:

  • Must have completed a UG degree with an aggregate ranging between 50% and 60% (for General category students) depending on the course
  • Those in the final year can also apply with a proof of eligibility

Q: How can I get admission in DTU?

A: 

To get admission to BTech at DTU, go to the site of JAC Delhi and register yourself and according to the schedule attend the counseling. On the day of counseling bring all the required certificates as mentioned on the website of JAC Delhi. The list will come out on the website itself and you are done after paying all the fees. The admission is solely dependent on the rank in JEE MAIN. Check all the cutoffs of the previous years before attending the counselling.

DTU Admission Process and Important Dates 2025

The mode of Delhi Technological University course admissions is online. Admission to various courses is based on merit and entrance exam scores. Delhi Technological University (DTU), which is well known for its BTech course, provides admission for BTech based on JEE Main results, JAC Delhi, and others. The JAC Delhi manages the entire counselling process. All other programmes at DTU need admission through national/university-level entrance exams, including UCEED, GATE, CAT, MAT, and others. However, there are a few MBA-specific programmes and a BBA programme that give admission based on a previous qualifying test (undergraduate level), followed by interview rounds. Step 2: Select the course and pay the application fee.
